A "memory leak in dpkt", really??
Skimming over https://github.com/felipems/cs244_final_project/blob/master/detector.py, they're creating dpkt IP or Ethernet object for every packet in the pcap and *appending those to a list*. The list grows, memory grows; it's by design. Every million entries they call gc.collect() to supposedly deal with the "memory leak".

```
        for ts, buf in pcap:
            if raw_ip:
                try:
                    ip = dpkt.ip.IP(buf)
                except :
                    continue           
            else:
                eth = dpkt.ethernet.Ethernet(buf)
                ip = eth.data
            all_packets.append(ip)             <<<---  "memory leak" here YEAH
            sample_packet(ip,bad_ips,good_ips);
            if len(all_packets)%1000000 ==0:             
                print len(all_packets)/1000000," million"
                gc.collect()
```

