I had fixed the problem at `tcconfig 0.20.0`
The cause of the problem is the handle-id conflict for tc rules.
`tcset` avoid this handle-id conflicts by checking existing handle-ids.
While scripts generated by `--tc-script` does not check the conflicts.
I had changed handle-id generation algorithm to be reduced the probability of conflicts.

