@kimkulling I'm not sure that I'd really call this a question, because I understand *what* is happening but I'm not convinced that what is happening makes sense. It's more of a discussion about what the intent is.

Practically, a model file probably shouldn't define an explicit identity transform. What we're running in to though, especially with engineering/CAD model editors like SolidWorks and ProE (I can't speak for other 3D asset editors) is that numerical approximations result in "identity-ish" transforms where some of the matrix diagonals are extremely small floating point numbers (on the order of 1e-8), so that when they get converted to .DAE it dumps an explicit identity transform matrix.

I think what it really comes down to is that I think assimp should handle explicit and implicit identity transforms the same way; it should either transform the implicit type to the model coordinate system or it should detect when the transform is identity and ignore it. Right now they behave differently even though the model file itself is trying to communicate the same thing in both cases.

