@eteq says in the other thread that he doesn't agree with this view (not unexpectedly, in light of discussion in the meantime), but my point was never mainly one of principle... We had a few years where most of the AstroPy people seemed not to grasp what `gwcs` is all about and kept brushing it under the carpet. It wasn't clear to me why that was. My concern/impression was that the name "wcs" might have contributed to general misunderstanding (probably along with a need for more documentation). I'd actually prefer to keep the name after calling it that for years, but was just worried about it giving people the wrong assumptions.

Anyway, I think this has been considered now, so documentation it is. Thanks.

An array of four kern values is frequently seen in RTL scripts, where both advance width and x-position are modified, here is an example:
`pos arAlefMadda arTeh  <-80 0 -80 0>;`

RTL kerning is usually wrapped into its own lookup:
```
feature kern {
    lookup ARABIC_KERNING {
        lookupflag RightToLeft IgnoreMarks;
        include (kern_arabic.fea)
    } ARABIC_KERNING;
} kern;

```

