@RonnyPfannschmidt you mention

>but why should we expose a class that adds no value to the user while locking us in to having it when all we really do is expose a few public methods

I would argue there is no "lock in". We can always change the type of `CallOutcome` without changing it's public *interface*; that's the beauty of duck typing ;)

Path should be
```
ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/cert.pem;
ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/privkey.pem;
```
This are Symlinks to the current Cert and Private Key and get updated on renewal, so you don't have to change it yourself.

@pde, I'll be honest and say that I don't know enough `git` fanciness to know how dangerous this is. I will say, however, that I saw @kuba's request for you not to do this and even the warning given in the stack overflow post you linked. To quote the most relevant part:

